  "texts": [
    "Corollary 7.2.",
    "There is an equivalenceExc 𝑑 * (Sp 𝜔, Sp) Q ≃ 1≤𝑖≤𝑑 Ch(Q[Σ 𝑖])of ∞-categories.We call the right-hand side an algebraic model of the ∞-category of rational 𝑑-excisive functors from spectra to spectra.Lemma 2.8.",
    "If 𝑖: C → D is an inclusion of a full subcategory such that there are no maps in D from any object 𝑐 ∈ C to any object 𝑑 ∈ D \\ C, then the ring map𝑖 *: 𝐴 Q (D) → 𝐴 Q (C)has kernel given by the free Q-module ⟨D \\ C⟩ generated by the set D \\ C of objects of D which are not objects of C.Proof.",
    "The functor 𝑖 *: 𝐴 Q (D) → 𝐴 Q (C) is the identity on the objects of C and zero on the objects of D which are not objects of C, hence each element of D \\ C lies in the kernel of 𝑖 *.",
    "The proof is then complete by observing that the dimension of the kernel and the dimension of the free Q-module ⟨D \\ C⟩ coincide."
  ],
